Thank you for your feedback.<p>JSON defines data. Human can write and read JSON files.<p>Add logic to the data seems to me easier for non-programmer to define what a program should do.<p>A basic JSON file for describing a circle could be:
    {
      &quot;radius&quot;: 5,
      &quot;diameter&quot; : 25
    }<p>With the following program, we can modify the radius and see the diameter value:
    {
      &quot;radius&quot;: &quot;att(5)&quot;,
      &quot;diameter&quot; : &quot;radius * radius&quot;
    }<p>It is closed to the original file.<p>The difference with solutions like Rails is that people do not need to know how to deploy an application.<p>In this project, people write in a JSON file and the application is automatically ready to serve the data.
